window.PEDIA_CONTENT = {"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anggrek_macan","title_id":"Anggrek Tebu","title_en":"Giant Orchid","subtitle_id":"Anggrek terbesar di dunia, berat dan tinggi!","subtitle_en":"The biggest orchid in the whole world!","sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Anggrek Tebu?","h_en":"What Is the Giant Orchid?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia. Orang juga memanggilnya Anggrek Raksasa, Anggrek Harimau, atau Ratu Anggrek. Tanaman ini bisa tumbuh sangat besar dan berat sekali. Bayangkan, ada yang beratnya lebih dari satu ton!","body_en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world. People also call it the Giant Orchid, Tiger Orchid, or Queen of Orchids. This plant can grow huge and very heavy. Imagine, some weigh more than one ton!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anggrek tebu tumbuh di hutan-hutan Asia Tenggara. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Indonesia, seperti di Sumatra, Jawa, Sulawesi, dan Kalimantan. Tanaman ini juga ada di Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, dan Malaysia. Ia suka tempat yang hangat dan terkena cahaya matahari.","body_en":"The giant orchid grows in the forests of Southeast Asia. You can find it in Indonesia, like in Sumatra, Java, Sulawesi, and Borneo. It also lives in Thailand, Myanmar, Vietnam, and Malaysia. It loves warm spots with plenty of sunshine."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anggrek ini bisa tumbuh setinggi rumah! Pernah ada yang mencapai lebih dari 7 meter. Batangnya yang tebal disebut pseudobulb dan bisa sepanjang 2,5 meter. Akarnya tumbuh seperti ikatan tebal yang menempel di pohon atau batu.","body_en":"This orchid can grow as tall as a house! One was even taller than 7 meters. Its thick stems are called pseudobulbs and can be 2.5 meters long. Its roots grow in thick bundles that cling to trees or rocks."},{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Bunga yang Istimewa","h_en":"Its Amazing Flowers","body_id":"Bunganya berwarna kuning cerah dengan bintik-bintik merah tua. Satu tangkai bisa punya hingga 80 bunga, dan satu tanaman bisa berbunga ribuan! Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap dua sampai empat tahun. Tapi saat mekar, bunganya tetap segar dan indah sampai berminggu-minggu.","body_en":"Its flowers are bright yellow with dark red spots. One stalk can have up to 80 flowers, and one plant can bloom thousands! This orchid blooms only once every two to four years. But when it blooms, the flowers stay fresh and pretty for weeks."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Kita Jaga!","h_en":"Let's Take Care of It!","body_id":"Anggrek tebu adalah harta alam Indonesia yang langka dan istimewa. Tanaman ini tumbuh lambat dan butuh hutan yang sehat untuk hidup. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap hijau. Dengan begitu, anak-anak masa depan juga bisa melihat raksasa cantik ini!","body_en":"The giant orchid is a rare and special treasure of Indonesia's nature. This plant grows slowly and needs healthy forests to live. We can help by keeping forests green. That way, future children can also see this beautiful giant!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Anggrek tebu adalah anggrek terbesar di dunia!","en":"The giant orchid is the biggest orchid in the world!"},{"id":"Pernah ada yang tingginya lebih dari 7 meter, setinggi rumah.","en":"One was over 7 meters tall, as tall as a house."},{"id":"Beratnya bisa lebih dari satu ton, seperti seekor sapi besar.","en":"It can weigh over one ton, like a big cow."},{"id":"Satu tanaman pernah berbunga sampai ribuan kuntum sekaligus!","en":"One plant once bloomed with thousands of flowers at once!"},{"id":"Anggrek ini hanya mekar sekali setiap 2 sampai 4 tahun.","en":"This orchid blooms only once every 2 to 4 years."},{"id":"Ada satu yang ditanam tahun 1861 dan masih hidup hingga kini!","en":"One planted in 1861 is still alive today!"}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/63ce9b63483762b3.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/0660c966a101239b.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/12eb3e4b61ec0623.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/4b5c177f2c83e0c2.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/17f94004bd703c64.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63ce9b63483762b3.jpg","credit":"Meneerke bloem","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0660c966a101239b.jpg","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/12eb3e4b61ec0623.jpg","credit":"Brutusaurus","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4b5c177f2c83e0c2.jpg","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/17f94004bd703c64.jpg","credit":"Die_Gartenlaube_(1897)_211.jpg: Ernst Keil's Nachfolger\nderivative work: Frédéri","license":"Public domain"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anggrek_tebu"},"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_anoa_sulawesi_1","title_id":"Anoa","title_en":"Anoa","subtitle_id":"Kerbau kerdil istimewa khas Pulau Sulawesi.","subtitle_en":"The special dwarf buffalo of Sulawesi.","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Anoa?","h_en":"What Is an Anoa?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kerbau mungil yang sering disebut kerbau kerdil. Bentuk tubuhnya mirip kerbau, tapi ukurannya jauh lebih kecil. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton di Indonesia. Karena hanya ada di sana, anoa disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The anoa is a tiny buffalo often called the dwarf buffalo. Its body looks like a buffalo, but it is much smaller. This animal lives only on Sulawesi Island and Buton Island in Indonesia. Because it lives only there, the anoa is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Anoa tinggal di dalam hutan hujan yang masih lebat dan jarang dilewati manusia. Pulau Sulawesi adalah rumah istimewa bagi banyak hewan yang hanya ada di sana. Salah satu kebiasaan favorit anoa adalah berkubang di lumpur. Berkubang membantu tubuhnya tetap sejuk dan bersih.","body_en":"The anoa lives deep in thick rainforests that people rarely visit. Sulawesi Island is a special home for many animals found nowhere else. One of the anoa's favorite habits is wallowing in mud. Wallowing helps keep its body cool and clean."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Special Features","body_id":"Anoa punya tanduk yang mengarah ke belakang dan dasarnya berbentuk seperti segitiga. Kepalanya mirip sapi, dan kakinya mirip banteng. Ada dua jenis anoa: anoa dataran rendah yang lebih besar, dan anoa pegunungan yang lebih kecil. Anoa pegunungan punya tanduk melingkar dan ekor pendek yang lembut.","body_en":"The anoa has horns that point backward with a triangle-shaped base. Its head looks like a cow's, and its legs look like a wild ox's. There are two kinds: the bigger lowland anoa and the smaller mountain anoa. The mountain anoa has curved horns and a short, soft tail."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Anoa adalah kebanggaan dan ciri khas Pulau Sulawesi. Ia tinggal di Wallacea, daerah unik yang penuh hewan dan tumbuhan yang hanya ada di sana. Anoa termasuk hewan yang pemalu dan suka menyendiri. Para ilmuwan menyayangi anoa karena ia sangat penting bagi alam Indonesia.","body_en":"The anoa is the pride and symbol of Sulawesi Island. It lives in Wallacea, a unique area full of animals and plants found only there. The anoa is a shy creature that likes to be alone. Scientists love the anoa because it is so important to Indonesia's nature."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Sekarang jumlah anoa semakin sedikit, jadi ia perlu kita lindungi. Hewan ini sudah dijaga oleh hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931. Anoa butuh hutan yang aman dan sehat untuk hidup. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu anoa terus berkembang biak dengan bahagia.","body_en":"Today there are fewer anoa, so we need to protect it. This animal has been guarded by Indonesian law since 1931. The anoa needs safe and healthy forests to live. By protecting forests, we help the anoa keep growing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Anoa adalah kerbau terkecil di dunia, disebut kerbau kerdil!","en":"The anoa is the smallest wild buffalo in the world, the dwarf buffalo!"},{"id":"Anoa hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi dan Pulau Buton.","en":"The anoa lives only on Sulawesi and Buton Islands."},{"id":"Ada dua jenis: anoa pegunungan dan anoa dataran rendah.","en":"There are two kinds: the mountain anoa and the lowland anoa."},{"id":"Anoa suka berkubang di lumpur agar tubuhnya tetap sejuk.","en":"The anoa loves to wallow in mud to keep its body cool."},{"id":"Tanduk anoa berbentuk segitiga di bagian dasarnya.","en":"The anoa's horns have a triangle shape at their base."},{"id":"Anoa sudah dilindungi hukum Indonesia sejak tahun 1931.","en":"The anoa has been protected by Indonesian law since 1931."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/9aadc51ed284047d.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/db38c2979418f98f.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/cc575629ae3b55cf.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/b769606dc03bc3bc.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/344b440b71935f33.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/659071a2263b3ae8.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9aadc51ed284047d.jpg","credit":"RianHS","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/db38c2979418f98f.jpg","credit":"Sakurai Midori","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/cc575629ae3b55cf.jpg","credit":"JERRYE AND ROY KLOTZ MD","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b769606dc03bc3bc.jpg","credit":"Bluemoose at English Wikipedia","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/344b440b71935f33.jpg","credit":"PenaTulip","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/659071a2263b3ae8.jpg","credit":"Farrel Nandito","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anoa"},"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa":{"id":"ensiklopedia_badak_jawa","title_id":"Badak Jawa","title_en":"Javan Rhinoceros","subtitle_id":"Badak bercula satu paling langka di dunia.","subtitle_en":"The rarest one-horned rhino in the world.","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Badak Jawa?","h_en":"What Is the Javan Rhino?","body_id":"Badak jawa adalah badak bercula satu yang tubuhnya cukup kecil di antara badak lainnya. Kulitnya tebal dan berlipat-lipat, seperti memakai baju pelindung dari baja. Hewan ini adalah salah satu badak paling langka di seluruh dunia. Culanya pendek, biasanya tidak lebih panjang dari sejengkal tangan.","body_en":"The Javan rhino is a one-horned rhino with a smaller body than most other rhinos. Its skin is thick and folded, like it is wearing armor made of steel. This animal is one of the rarest rhinos in the whole world. Its horn is short, usually no longer than a hand's span."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hari ini, semua badak jawa liar hanya tinggal di satu tempat: Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon. Tempat ini berada di ujung paling barat Pulau Jawa, Indonesia. Dulu badak jawa hidup di banyak negara Asia, tapi sekarang tinggal sedikit. Ujung Kulon bahkan diakui dunia sebagai Situs Warisan Dunia UNESCO.","body_en":"Today, all wild Javan rhinos live in just one place: Ujung Kulon National Park. This park is on the far western tip of Java Island, Indonesia. Long ago Javan rhinos lived in many Asian countries, but now only a few remain. Ujung Kulon is even recognized as a UNESCO World Heritage Site."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Badak jawa suka tinggal di hutan dataran rendah yang lebat dan padang rumput yang basah. Hewan ini senang menyendiri dan biasanya berjalan-jalan sendirian. Mereka suka berkubang di lumpur untuk mendinginkan tubuh. Badak dewasa hampir tidak punya musuh, dan bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun!","body_en":"The Javan rhino loves thick lowland forests and wet grasslands. This animal enjoys being alone and usually wanders by itself. It likes to wallow in mud to cool down its body. Adult rhinos have almost no enemies, and can live up to 30 to 45 years!"},{"icon":"photo_camera","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Badak jawa sangat langka, jadi para ilmuwan jarang melihatnya langsung. Mereka memakai kamera jebakan yang memotret saat badak lewat. Pada tahun 2011, kamera berhasil merekam ibu-ibu badak bersama anaknya. Itu berita yang membahagiakan, karena membuktikan badak jawa masih punya bayi di alam liar!","body_en":"The Javan rhino is so rare that scientists rarely see it in person. They use camera traps that take photos when a rhino walks by. In 2011, cameras filmed mother rhinos with their babies. That was happy news, because it proved Javan rhinos still have babies in the wild!"},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Karena jumlahnya tinggal sedikit, badak jawa sangat butuh perlindungan kita. Para penjaga taman bekerja keras menjaga mereka tetap aman. Menjaga hutan Ujung Kulon tetap sehat sangat penting bagi badak. Kalau kita semua peduli, badak jawa bisa terus hidup untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"Because so few are left, the Javan rhino really needs our protection. Park rangers work hard to keep them safe. Keeping the Ujung Kulon forest healthy is very important for the rhinos. If we all care, the Javan rhino can keep living for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Badak jawa adalah salah satu badak paling langka di dunia!","en":"The Javan rhino is one of the rarest rhinos in the world!"},{"id":"Semua badak jawa liar hanya hidup di Taman Nasional Ujung Kulon.","en":"All wild Javan rhinos live only in Ujung Kulon National Park."},{"id":"Kulitnya berlipat-lipat seperti memakai baju zirah dari baja.","en":"Its folded skin looks like armor made of steel."},{"id":"Badak jawa bisa hidup sampai 30 hingga 45 tahun di alam liar.","en":"The Javan rhino can live 30 to 45 years in the wild."},{"id":"Para ilmuwan memakai kamera jebakan untuk mengintip badak.","en":"Scientists use camera traps to peek at the rhinos."},{"id":"Tahun 2011, kamera merekam bayi badak bersama ibunya!","en":"In 2011, cameras filmed baby rhinos with their moms!"}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/360d5dadfb2dfc50.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/01c213da6cb774ae.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/17b1a5b62b81d39f.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/01c213da6cb774ae.jpg","credit":"T.Dixon. The Zoological Society of London","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/360d5dadfb2dfc50.jpg","credit":"Jo Oh 21:38, 19 January 2006 (UTC)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/17b1a5b62b81d39f.jpg","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Badak_jawa"},"ensiklopedia_bekantan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bekantan","title_id":"Bekantan","title_en":"Proboscis Monkey","subtitle_id":"Monyet berhidung panjang khas Pulau Kalimantan.","subtitle_en":"The long-nosed monkey of Borneo.","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Bekantan?","h_en":"What Is the Proboscis Monkey?","body_id":"Bekantan adalah monyet berhidung panjang dengan rambut hitam kemerahan. Hidung yang besar dan panjang hanya dimiliki bekantan jantan. Orang juga memanggilnya kera belanda atau monyet belanda. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan, jadi disebut hewan endemik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey is a long-nosed monkey with reddish-black fur. Only the male proboscis monkeys have the big, long nose. People also call it the Dutch monkey or long-nosed monkey. This animal lives only on Borneo, so it is called an endemic animal."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bekantan tinggal di hutan, rawa, dan hutan dekat pantai di Kalimantan. Kamu bisa menemukannya di Kalimantan Selatan, Timur, dan Utara. Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Provinsi Kalimantan Selatan. Ia berbagi rumah dengan teman-temannya seperti orangutan dan lutung kelabu.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in forests, swamps, and coastal forests in Borneo. You can find it in South, East, and North Kalimantan. The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan Province. It shares its home with friends like orangutans and gray langurs."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Perut Buncit","h_en":"Food & Its Big Belly","body_id":"Bekantan suka makan buah, biji-bijian, dan aneka daun. Daun yang dimakannya menghasilkan banyak gas saat dicerna. Itulah kenapa perut bekantan terlihat buncit dan besar. Jadi, perut buncit itu adalah ciri khas yang lucu dari bekantan!","body_en":"The proboscis monkey loves to eat fruits, seeds, and many kinds of leaves. The leaves it eats make lots of gas when digested. That is why the proboscis monkey has a round, big belly. So its big belly is a funny special feature of the proboscis monkey!"},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Perenang yang Hebat","h_en":"A Great Swimmer","body_id":"Bekantan hidup berkelompok, biasanya 10 sampai 32 monyet bersama. Mereka juga jago berenang, bahkan menyeberang dari satu pulau ke pulau lain! Di sela jari kakinya ada selaput tipis yang membantunya berenang. Hidungnya punya semacam katup, jadi ia bisa menyelam beberapa detik.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey lives in groups, usually 10 to 32 monkeys together. They are also great swimmers, even crossing from one island to another! Between their toes is a thin web that helps them swim. Their nose has a kind of valve, so they can dive for a few seconds."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bekantan perlu kita lindungi karena hutannya semakin berkurang. Kabar baiknya, di Kalimantan Selatan jumlah bekantan naik dari sekitar 3.000 menjadi 4.000 ekor. Ini terjadi karena banyak orang ikut menjaga mereka. Kalau kita menjaga hutan, bekantan bisa terus berenang dan bermain dengan bahagia.","body_en":"The proboscis monkey needs our protection because its forests are shrinking. The good news is that in South Kalimantan their number rose from about 3,000 to 4,000. This happened because many people helped protect them. If we protect the forests, proboscis monkeys can keep swimming and playing happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Hanya bekantan jantan yang punya hidung panjang dan besar!","en":"Only male proboscis monkeys have the long, big nose!"},{"id":"Bekantan hanya hidup di Pulau Kalimantan.","en":"The proboscis monkey lives only on Borneo."},{"id":"Perutnya buncit karena banyak makan daun yang menghasilkan gas.","en":"Its belly is big from eating many gassy leaves."},{"id":"Bekantan jago berenang dan punya selaput di sela jari kaki.","en":"The proboscis monkey is a great swimmer with webbed toes."},{"id":"Bekantan adalah hewan kebanggaan Kalimantan Selatan.","en":"The proboscis monkey is the pride animal of South Kalimantan."},{"id":"Jumlahnya di Kalimantan Selatan naik menjadi sekitar 4.000 ekor!","en":"Their number in South Kalimantan rose to about 4,000!"}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/e136b48c3214f29a.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/49ea08d34756f739.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9361a077e9d3bc15.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/91931c7b866f4c18.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/574c0804ed7e522c.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/585d5d0fc86c23e0.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e136b48c3214f29a.jpg","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/49ea08d34756f739.jpg","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9361a077e9d3bc15.jpg","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/91931c7b866f4c18.jpg","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/574c0804ed7e522c.jpg","credit":"Ade Putri Amelia Az-Zahra","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/585d5d0fc86c23e0.jpg","credit":"Agoes Suwondo","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bekantan"},"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai":{"id":"ensiklopedia_bunga_bangkai","title_id":"Bunga Bangkai Raksasa","title_en":"Giant Corpse Flower","subtitle_id":"Bunga raksasa berbau busuk dari hutan Sumatra!","subtitle_en":"A giant smelly flower from Sumatra's forests!","sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Bunga Bangkai?","h_en":"What Is the Corpse Flower?","body_id":"Bunga bangkai raksasa (Amorphophallus titanum) adalah tumbuhan dengan bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia. Bunga ini berasal dari Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Namanya 'bunga bangkai' karena baunya seperti bangkai yang busuk!","body_en":"The giant corpse flower (Amorphophallus titanum) is the plant with the largest cluster of flowers in the world. It comes from the island of Sumatra in Indonesia. It is called the 'corpse flower' because it smells like rotting meat!"},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Bunga ini tumbuh di hutan hujan tropis Sumatra, seperti di Kerinci dan Lampung. Ia suka tanah berkapur dan tempat yang lembap di bawah pepohonan besar. Kamu juga bisa melihatnya mekar di Kebun Raya Bogor dan Cibodas.","body_en":"This flower grows in the tropical rainforests of Sumatra, like in Kerinci and Lampung. It likes limestone soil and damp, shady spots under tall trees. You can also see it bloom at the Bogor and Cibodas Botanical Gardens."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bunga bangkai bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi, bahkan lebih tinggi dari orang dewasa! Bagian tengahnya yang menjulang disebut spadix, dikelilingi kelopak besar berwarna merah hati dan hijau. Di bawah tanah ada umbi raksasa yang menyimpan makanannya.","body_en":"The corpse flower can grow very tall, even taller than a grown-up! Its tall middle part is called the spadix, surrounded by a big petal that is dark red and green. Underground there is a giant tuber that stores its food."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Kapan Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"When It Blooms & Its Smell","body_id":"Bunga ini sangat sabar! Ia menyimpan makanan di umbinya selama bertahun-tahun, lalu mekar hanya sekitar 7 hari saja. Saat mekar, baunya yang busuk mengundang kumbang dan lalat untuk membantu menyerbukinya.","body_en":"This flower is very patient! It stores food in its tuber for years, then blooms for only about 7 days. When it blooms, its stinky smell invites beetles and flies to help pollinate it."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Bunga bangkai liar makin sedikit karena hutannya berubah menjadi kebun dan rumah. Burung rangkong membantu menyebar bijinya. Dengan menjaga hutan dan burung rangkong, kita bisa membantu bunga ajaib ini tetap mekar untuk anak-anak masa depan.","body_en":"Wild corpse flowers are getting rarer because their forests are turning into farms and houses. Hornbill birds help spread their seeds. By protecting the forest and the hornbills, we can help this amazing flower keep blooming for children of the future."}],"facts":[{"id":"Ini adalah bunga majemuk terbesar di dunia!","en":"It is the largest cluster of flowers in the world!"},{"id":"Baunya seperti daging busuk untuk menarik lalat dan kumbang.","en":"It smells like rotten meat to attract flies and beetles."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar 7 hari saja.","en":"Its flower blooms for only about 7 days."},{"id":"Umbinya bisa seberat 100 kilogram di bawah tanah!","en":"Its underground tuber can weigh up to 100 kilograms!"},{"id":"Bunga ini bisa tunggu bertahun-tahun sebelum mekar.","en":"This flower can wait for years before it blooms."},{"id":"Tumbuhan ini hanya ada di Indonesia.","en":"This plant is found only in Indonesia."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/f726ea8c7f07ce2d.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/e00355769094147e.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/a62a3929167cadac.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/c4896d72d51fd585.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/3048cd57126f2150.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/f328495018035d73.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f726ea8c7f07ce2d.jpg","credit":"Credits: US Botanic Garden.","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e00355769094147e.jpg","credit":"Shubert Ciencia from Nueva Ecija, Philippines","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a62a3929167cadac.jpg","credit":"Steve Fitzgerald","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c4896d72d51fd585.jpg","credit":"Björn S...","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3048cd57126f2150.jpg","credit":"Foto © W. Barthlott","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f328495018035d73.jpg","credit":"Jari Poutanen","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bunga_bangkai_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_burung_maleo_1","title_id":"Burung Maleo","title_en":"Maleo Bird","subtitle_id":"Burung unik yang menetaskan telur dari panas bumi!","subtitle_en":"A unique bird that hatches eggs with earth's heat!","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Burung Maleo?","h_en":"What Is the Maleo Bird?","body_id":"Maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) adalah burung istimewa yang juga disebut kalkun sikat. Ia termasuk kelompok burung megapoda. Maleo senkawor hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia, dan tidak ada di tempat lain di dunia.","body_en":"The maleo (Macrocephalon maleo) is a special bird also called the brush-turkey. It belongs to a group of birds called megapodes. The maleo lives only on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia, and nowhere else in the world."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Maleo tinggal di hutan tropis Sulawesi. Mereka suka pergi ke pantai berpasir atau tanah hangat dekat sumber panas bumi. Tempat hangat ini sangat penting untuk telur-telur mereka.","body_en":"The maleo lives in the tropical forests of Sulawesi. They like to go to sandy beaches or warm ground near volcanic hot spots. These warm places are very important for their eggs."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Maleo punya bulu hitam, dada putih kemerahan, dan ciri khas berupa benjolan keras di kepalanya. Benjolan ini membuatnya terlihat seperti memakai topi! Kakinya kuat untuk menggali tanah dan pasir.","body_en":"The maleo has black feathers, a pinkish-white chest, and a special hard bump on its head. This bump makes it look like it is wearing a hat! Its legs are strong for digging in soil and sand."},{"icon":"egg","h_id":"Telur Ajaib","h_en":"Magic Eggs","body_id":"Maleo tidak mengerami telurnya sendiri. Ia mengubur telur di pasir hangat atau tanah dekat panas bumi, lalu panas alam itu yang menetaskannya! Telur maleo sangat besar, jauh lebih besar dari telur ayam.","body_en":"The maleo does not sit on its eggs. It buries them in warm sand or soil near volcanic heat, and nature's warmth hatches them! Maleo eggs are very big, much larger than chicken eggs."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Burung maleo terancam karena telurnya sering diambil dan hutannya berkurang. Anak maleo harus mandiri sejak menetas. Dengan menjaga sarang dan hutan Sulawesi, kita bisa membantu burung unik ini tetap ada.","body_en":"The maleo bird is threatened because its eggs are often taken and its forests are shrinking. Baby maleos must take care of themselves from the moment they hatch. By protecting their nests and Sulawesi's forests, we can help this unique bird survive."}],"facts":[{"id":"Maleo hanya hidup di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia!","en":"The maleo lives only on Sulawesi Island, Indonesia!"},{"id":"Mereka menetaskan telur memakai panas bumi dan matahari.","en":"They hatch eggs using the heat of the earth and sun."},{"id":"Telur maleo jauh lebih besar daripada telur ayam.","en":"Maleo eggs are much bigger than chicken eggs."},{"id":"Anak maleo bisa langsung terbang dan mencari makan sendiri.","en":"Baby maleos can fly and find food on their own right away."},{"id":"Maleo punya benjolan keras seperti topi di kepalanya.","en":"The maleo has a hard, hat-like bump on its head."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/fddc7ccf6df38c39.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/1c5a3301bc8d33af.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9896525663b797d0.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/abe550888eb52d60.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9d7670cdac1a56df.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/f1e18ca111aca999.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9d7670cdac1a56df.jpg","credit":"Bernard DUPONT from FRANCE","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f1e18ca111aca999.jpg","credit":"JJ Harrison (https://www.jjharrison.com.au/)","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/fddc7ccf6df38c39.jpg","credit":"Jean-Paul Boerekamps","license":"CC0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1c5a3301bc8d33af.jpg","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9896525663b797d0.jpg","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/abe550888eb52d60.jpg","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maleo"},"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih":{"id":"ensiklopedia_cendrawasih","title_id":"Cendrawasih","title_en":"Bird-of-Paradise","subtitle_id":"Burung surga cantik dari tanah Papua!","subtitle_en":"The beautiful bird of paradise from Papua!","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Cendrawasih?","h_en":"What Is the Bird-of-Paradise?","body_id":"Cendrawasih adalah burung pengicau cantik dari keluarga Paradisaeidae. Banyak orang menyebutnya 'burung surga' karena bulunya yang indah dan berwarna-warni. Ada banyak jenisnya, seperti cendrawasih merah, kuning, raja, dan kaisar.","body_en":"The bird-of-paradise is a beautiful songbird from the Paradisaeidae family. Many people call it the 'bird of heaven' because of its lovely, colorful feathers. There are many kinds, like the red, yellow, king, and emperor birds-of-paradise."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Cendrawasih hidup di hutan-hutan lebat di Papua, Indonesia, dan pulau-pulau di sekitarnya. Mereka suka tinggal tinggi di atas pepohonan hutan hujan tropis. Karena keindahannya, burung ini menjadi kebanggaan tanah Papua.","body_en":"Birds-of-paradise live in the thick forests of Papua, Indonesia, and nearby islands. They like to stay high up in the trees of the tropical rainforest. Because of their beauty, these birds are the pride of Papua."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan memiliki bulu yang sangat indah dengan warna-warna cerah seperti merah, kuning, dan hijau. Beberapa punya bulu panjang yang menjuntai seperti pita atau kawat. Bulu cantik ini hanya dimiliki oleh burung jantan.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise have very beautiful feathers in bright colors like red, yellow, and green. Some have long feathers that flow like ribbons or wires. These lovely feathers belong only to the male birds."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Menari","h_en":"Their Dancing Habit","body_id":"Cendrawasih jantan suka menari untuk menarik perhatian betina! Mereka memamerkan bulu indahnya sambil bergoyang di atas dahan. Mereka memakan buah-buahan dan serangga kecil di hutan.","body_en":"Male birds-of-paradise love to dance to attract the females! They show off their beautiful feathers while swaying on the branches. They eat fruits and small insects in the forest."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Cendrawasih harus kita jaga agar tidak punah. Mereka terancam karena hutan tempat tinggalnya berkurang dan perburuan bulunya. Dengan menjaga hutan Papua, kita membantu burung surga ini terus terbang bebas dan menari.","body_en":"We must protect birds-of-paradise so they do not disappear. They are threatened because their forest homes are shrinking and people hunt them for their feathers. By protecting Papua's forests, we help these heavenly birds keep flying free and dancing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Cendrawasih dijuluki 'burung surga' karena keindahannya.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is nicknamed the 'bird of heaven' for its beauty."},{"id":"Burung jantan menari untuk memikat pasangannya.","en":"Male birds dance to win a partner."},{"id":"Hanya burung jantan yang punya bulu hias super cantik.","en":"Only the male birds have super pretty show feathers."},{"id":"Cendrawasih adalah lambang kebanggaan tanah Papua.","en":"The bird-of-paradise is a symbol of pride for Papua."},{"id":"Ada belasan jenis cendrawasih di Indonesia.","en":"There are over a dozen kinds of birds-of-paradise in Indonesia."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/47ba731e94dfca1a.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/1a13738e3075d8d5.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/b137ef678195257f.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/892238c9389bd6e6.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/92e7f1db2270f296.png","app/assets/img/wiki/b545725c50aa8cab.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1a13738e3075d8d5.jpg","credit":"Albertus Seba (1665 - 1736) – Artist (German) Born in Etzel, Germany. Died in Am","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/47ba731e94dfca1a.jpg","credit":"Philip Nalangan","license":"CC BY 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b137ef678195257f.jpg","credit":"Ulisse Aldrovandi","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/92e7f1db2270f296.png","credit":"Houseplants Nook","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/892238c9389bd6e6.jpg","credit":"Author unknown","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b545725c50aa8cab.jpg","credit":"H. Zell","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cenderawasih_%28disambiguasi%29"},"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra":{"id":"ensiklopedia_gajah_sumatra","title_id":"Gajah Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Elephant","subtitle_id":"Mamalia terbesar dan tercerdas di Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"Indonesia's biggest and smartest mammal!","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Gajah Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Elephant?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra (Elephas maximus sumatranus) adalah jenis gajah Asia yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra. Ia adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia! Tubuhnya sedikit lebih kecil daripada gajah dari India.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant (Elephas maximus sumatranus) is a kind of Asian elephant that lives only on the island of Sumatra. It is the biggest mammal in Indonesia! Its body is a little smaller than the elephant from India."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Gajah sumatra hidup di hutan-hutan luas, seperti hutan rawa, hutan gambut, dan hutan hujan dataran rendah. Mereka butuh wilayah jelajah yang sangat luas untuk berkeliling. Mereka juga suka tempat yang dekat dengan sumber air.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant lives in wide forests, like swamp forests, peat forests, and lowland rainforests. They need a very large area to roam around. They also like places close to water."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Gajah sumatra bisa setinggi 3,5 meter di bahu dan beratnya mencapai beberapa ton! Telinganya yang besar membantunya mendengar dan menjaga tubuh tetap sejuk. Belalainya yang panjang dipakai untuk meraih makanan dan air seperti tangan.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant can be 3.5 meters tall at the shoulder and weigh several tons! Its big ears help it hear well and keep its body cool. Its long trunk is used to grab food and water like a hand."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Gajah sumatra adalah herbivora, jadi ia hanya makan tumbuhan! Ia suka rumput, semak muda, daun, dan kulit kayu yang lembut. Gajah sangat cerdas dan punya otak besar. Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan sebelum lahir.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is a herbivore, so it eats only plants! It likes grass, young shrubs, leaves, and soft bark. Elephants are very smart and have a big brain. A baby elephant grows for 22 months before it is born."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Gajah sumatra sangat terancam punah karena hutannya banyak berubah menjadi perkebunan. Gajah penting sekali karena membantu menyebarkan biji tanaman di hutan. Dengan menjaga hutan dan hidup damai bersama gajah, kita bisa menyelamatkan sahabat raksasa ini.","body_en":"The Sumatran elephant is highly endangered because much of its forest has been turned into plantations. Elephants are very important because they help spread plant seeds in the forest. By protecting the forest and living peacefully with elephants, we can save this giant friend."}],"facts":[{"id":"Gajah sumatra adalah mamalia terbesar di Indonesia!","en":"The Sumatran elephant is the biggest mammal in Indonesia!"},{"id":"Otaknya lebih besar dari mamalia darat lainnya.","en":"Its brain is bigger than other land mammals'."},{"id":"Bayi gajah dikandung selama 22 bulan, hampir 2 tahun!","en":"A baby elephant grows for 22 months, almost 2 years!"},{"id":"Gajah bisa hidup sampai sekitar 70 tahun.","en":"Elephants can live up to about 70 years."},{"id":"Gajah membantu menanam hutan dengan menyebar biji.","en":"Elephants help grow forests by spreading seeds."},{"id":"Belalai gajah dipakai seperti tangan untuk meraup makanan.","en":"An elephant's trunk works like a hand to scoop up food."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/990889d90c287246.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/22f9acabeae4d8b6.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/46667cb5f2bff657.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/88199b85ba995c0c.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/990889d90c287246.jpg","credit":"Léodras","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/22f9acabeae4d8b6.jpg","credit":"Afrianto silalahi","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/46667cb5f2bff657.jpg","credit":"Panyahatan Siregar","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/88199b85ba995c0c.jpg","credit":"kusuma wijaya","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gajah_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_harimau_sumatra_1","title_id":"Harimau Sumatra","title_en":"Sumatran Tiger","subtitle_id":"Kucing besar penjaga hutan Pulau Sumatra","subtitle_en":"The big cat guarding Sumatra's forests","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Harimau Sumatra?","h_en":"What Is the Sumatran Tiger?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah kucing besar yang hanya hidup di Pulau Sumatra, Indonesia. Ia adalah harimau paling kecil di antara semua jenis harimau di dunia. Tubuhnya yang mungil membuatnya gesit menjelajahi hutan. Ia satu-satunya harimau sunda yang masih hidup sampai sekarang.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a big cat that lives only on the island of Sumatra, Indonesia. It is the smallest of all tiger types in the world. Its small body makes it quick and nimble in the forest. It is the only Sunda tiger still alive today."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Harimau sumatra tinggal di hutan-hutan Pulau Sumatra. Ia bisa hidup di hutan dataran rendah sampai hutan di pegunungan. Banyak yang tinggal di taman nasional dan cagar alam yang dilindungi. Di jari-jarinya ada selaput, jadi ia juga pandai berenang!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger lives in the forests of Sumatra island. It can live in lowland forests all the way up to mountain forests. Many live in protected national parks and nature reserves. It has webbing between its toes, so it is also a great swimmer!"},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu harimau sumatra berwarna oranye tua dengan garis hitam yang lebar dan rapat. Warnanya paling gelap di antara semua harimau. Harimau jantan punya lebih banyak janggut dan surai di wajahnya. Loreng ini membantunya bersembunyi di balik bayang-bayang hutan.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger's fur is deep orange with wide, close-set black stripes. Its color is the darkest of all tigers. Males have more beard and mane around the face. These stripes help it hide among the forest shadows."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Harimau sumatra adalah pemburu yang sabar dan pandai. Ia memakan babi hutan, rusa, unggas, dan kadang ikan. Karena ia berburu, jumlah hewan lain di hutan tetap seimbang. Induk harimau biasanya melahirkan 2 atau 3 anak yang sangat lucu.","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is a patient and clever hunter. It eats wild boar, deer, birds, and sometimes fish. Because it hunts, the number of other animals in the forest stays balanced. A mother tiger usually has 2 or 3 adorable cubs."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Harimau sumatra sangat langka, hanya tersisa sekitar 400-500 ekor di alam liar. Hutannya makin sempit karena ditebang, dan ini membuatnya sulit mencari rumah. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap lestari. Dengan kerja sama, harimau gagah ini bisa terus hidup bahagia!","body_en":"The Sumatran tiger is very rare, with only about 400-500 left in the wild. Its forest is shrinking because of logging, making it hard to find a home. We can help by keeping forests healthy and green. Working together, this brave tiger can keep living happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Harimau sumatra adalah harimau terkecil di dunia!","en":"The Sumatran tiger is the smallest tiger in the world!"},{"id":"Warna bulunya paling gelap di antara semua harimau.","en":"Its fur is the darkest of all tigers."},{"id":"Ada selaput di jari kakinya supaya bisa berenang cepat.","en":"It has webbed toes so it can swim fast."},{"id":"Loreng setiap harimau berbeda, seperti sidik jari manusia.","en":"Every tiger's stripes are unique, like a human fingerprint."},{"id":"Di alam liar, harimau sumatra bisa hidup sampai 15 tahun.","en":"In the wild, a Sumatran tiger can live up to 15 years."},{"id":"Anak harimau membuka matanya pada hari kesepuluh.","en":"Tiger cubs open their eyes on the tenth day."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/5e0df62e7237ee3e.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/2ea82aae5a4338e2.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/3deabfd4d2601a73.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/f914dca6ad1808d1.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/5c5afa2d73eaab29.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/78f7dbbcfec56188.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5e0df62e7237ee3e.jpg","credit":"Captain Herbert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f914dca6ad1808d1.jpg","credit":"Unknown authorUnknown author","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/2ea82aae5a4338e2.jpg","credit":"Nichollas Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/78f7dbbcfec56188.jpg","credit":"J.T. (Jan Theodoor) Ponse (Fotograaf/photographer).","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5c5afa2d73eaab29.jpg","credit":"Official Website of Ministry of Environment and Forestry Indonesia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3deabfd4d2601a73.jpg","credit":"Moonlight0551 from Australia","license":"CC BY 2.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harimau_sumatra"},"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hiu_paus","title_id":"Hiu Paus","title_en":"Whale Shark","subtitle_id":"Ikan terbesar di dunia yang ramah","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest, friendliest fish","sections":[{"icon":"waves","h_id":"Apa Itu Hiu Paus?","h_en":"What Is the Whale Shark?","body_id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di seluruh dunia! Walaupun namanya hiu, ia lembut dan tidak berbahaya bagi manusia. Ia disebut hiu paus karena tubuhnya besar dan cara makannya menyaring air laut seperti paus. Di Indonesia ia juga dipanggil hiu tutul karena punggungnya bertotol.","body_en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the whole world! Even though it is a shark, it is gentle and harmless to people. It is called a whale shark because of its huge body and the way it eats by filtering seawater, just like a whale. In Indonesia it is also called 'hiu tutul' because of the spots on its back."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Hiu paus berenang di lautan tropis yang hangat di seluruh dunia. Ia suka mengembara jauh dan termasuk ikan yang suka bermigrasi. Di Indonesia, hiu paus bisa ditemui di banyak tempat penyelaman. Ia bahkan bisa menyelam sangat dalam ke dasar laut.","body_en":"The whale shark swims in warm, tropical oceans all around the world. It loves to wander far and is a fish that migrates. In Indonesia, whale sharks can be spotted at many diving spots. It can even dive very deep down into the sea."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Tubuh hiu paus berwarna abu-abu dengan perut putih. Punggungnya penuh bintik dan garis putih kekuningan yang tampak seperti taburan bintang di langit. Pola bintik ini berbeda pada setiap hiu, seperti sidik jari. Mulutnya sangat lebar dan datar di ujung kepalanya.","body_en":"The whale shark's body is gray with a white belly. Its back is covered in yellowish-white spots and stripes that look like stars sprinkled across the sky. This spot pattern is different on every shark, like a fingerprint. Its mouth is very wide and flat at the front of its head."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Hiu paus makan dengan cara menyaring air laut lewat mulutnya yang besar. Makanan kesukaannya adalah plankton, yaitu makhluk laut yang sangat kecil. Ia berenang pelan dengan mulut terbuka lebar, lalu air keluar lewat insang dan makanan tertinggal. Walau giginya banyak, ia tidak memakainya untuk mengunyah.","body_en":"The whale shark eats by filtering seawater through its big mouth. Its favorite food is plankton, which are tiny sea creatures. It swims slowly with its mouth wide open, then water flows out through its gills while the food stays behind. Even though it has many teeth, it does not use them to chew."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa?","h_en":"Why Is It Special?","body_id":"Hiu paus sangat ramah, kadang membiarkan penyelam berenang di dekatnya. Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun dan dipercaya sudah ada sejak 60 juta tahun lalu. Sayangnya, ia bisa terancam karena tertangkap jaring nelayan. Yuk, kita jaga laut tetap bersih agar raksasa lembut ini terus berenang bahagia!","body_en":"The whale shark is very friendly and sometimes lets divers swim near it. It can live up to 70 years and is believed to have existed since 60 million years ago. Sadly, it can be in danger from getting caught in fishing nets. Let's keep our oceans clean so this gentle giant can keep swimming happily!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Hiu paus adalah ikan terbesar di dunia!","en":"The whale shark is the biggest fish in the world!"},{"id":"Ia bisa hidup sampai 70 tahun.","en":"It can live up to 70 years."},{"id":"Pola bintik di punggungnya unik, seperti sidik jari.","en":"The spots on its back are unique, like a fingerprint."},{"id":"Mulutnya bisa selebar hingga 1,5 meter!","en":"Its mouth can be very wide for filtering food!"},{"id":"Walau besar, hiu paus jinak dan tidak berbahaya.","en":"Despite its size, the whale shark is tame and harmless."},{"id":"Hiu paus suka makan plankton yang sangat kecil.","en":"Whale sharks love eating tiny plankton."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/0db4e5bbcb6017eb.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/ef8e657a0d08a540.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/f1f1e725e5bec58e.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/e82213409de96120.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/ea8a69023305e034.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/817902667e46f839.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0db4e5bbcb6017eb.jpg","credit":"User:Zac Wolf (original), en:User:Stefan (cropping)","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ea8a69023305e034.jpg","credit":"Jaontiveros","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/f1f1e725e5bec58e.jpg","credit":"Aoates","license":"CC BY 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/817902667e46f839.jpg","credit":"Jaontiveros","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/ef8e657a0d08a540.jpg","credit":"Zac Wolf","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e82213409de96120.jpg","credit":"Jordy Meow","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hiu_paus"},"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove":{"id":"ensiklopedia_hutan_mangrove","title_id":"Hutan Mangrove","title_en":"Mangrove Forest","subtitle_id":"Hutan ajaib penjaga pantai dan rumah satwa","subtitle_en":"Magical coastal forest, home to wildlife","sections":[{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Apa Itu Hutan Mangrove?","h_en":"What Is a Mangrove Forest?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove, atau hutan bakau, adalah hutan istimewa yang tumbuh di tepi laut. Pohon-pohonnya berdiri di tanah berlumpur yang sering tergenang air pasang. Hanya tumbuhan khusus yang bisa hidup di sini karena airnya asin. Hutan ini sering tumbuh di teluk yang tenang dan di muara sungai.","body_en":"A mangrove forest is a special forest that grows along the seashore. Its trees stand in muddy soil that is often flooded by the tide. Only special plants can live here because the water is salty. These forests often grow in calm bays and at river mouths."},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Tumbuhnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Grow?","body_id":"Hutan mangrove tumbuh di tempat-tempat yang hangat di dekat garis khatulistiwa. Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di seluruh dunia! Hutan ini banyak ditemukan di pantai timur Sumatra, Kalimantan, dan Papua. Seperempat hutan mangrove dunia ada di negara kita.","body_en":"Mangrove forests grow in warm places near the equator. Indonesia has the largest mangrove forests in the whole world! They are found along the east coast of Sumatra, in Kalimantan, and in Papua. A quarter of the world's mangroves are in our country."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Pohon yang Hebat","h_en":"Amazing Trees","body_id":"Pohon bakau punya akar khusus yang menjulur seperti kaki-kaki yang kokoh. Akar ini membantunya berdiri kuat di lumpur yang lembek. Ada banyak jenis pohon mangrove, dan sekitar 39 jenis tumbuh di Indonesia. Pohon-pohon ini tumbuh berlapis-lapis, dari tepi laut sampai ke daratan.","body_en":"Mangrove trees have special roots that stretch out like sturdy legs. These roots help them stand strong in the soft mud. There are many kinds of mangrove trees, and about 39 kinds grow in Indonesia. They grow in layers, from the seashore all the way inland."},{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Rumah Banyak Hewan","h_en":"Home to Many Animals","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah rumah yang nyaman bagi banyak hewan. Ikan kecil, kepiting, dan udang bersembunyi di antara akar-akarnya. Burung-burung indah, seperti jalak bali, juga suka tinggal di sini. Tempat ini seperti taman bermain yang penuh kehidupan!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a cozy home for many animals. Small fish, crabs, and shrimp hide among its roots. Beautiful birds, like the Bali myna, also love to live here. This place is like a playground full of life!"},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Pelindung Pantai","h_en":"Guardian of the Coast","body_id":"Hutan mangrove adalah perisai alami yang melindungi pantai. Akar-akarnya yang rapat menahan ombak besar agar tidak merusak daratan. Hutan ini juga mencegah tanah pantai terkikis air laut. Yuk, kita jaga hutan mangrove agar pantai dan hewan-hewannya tetap aman!","body_en":"The mangrove forest is a natural shield that protects the coast. Its thick roots hold back big waves so they cannot harm the land. The forest also stops the shore from being washed away by the sea. Let's protect mangrove forests so our coasts and animals stay safe!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Indonesia punya hutan mangrove terluas di dunia!","en":"Indonesia has the largest mangrove forest in the world!"},{"id":"Seperempat mangrove dunia ada di Indonesia.","en":"A quarter of the world's mangroves are in Indonesia."},{"id":"Akar bakau menahan ombak besar agar pantai aman.","en":"Mangrove roots hold back big waves to keep the coast safe."},{"id":"Sekitar 39 jenis pohon bakau tumbuh di Indonesia.","en":"About 39 kinds of mangrove trees grow in Indonesia."},{"id":"Ikan, kepiting, dan burung tinggal di antara akarnya.","en":"Fish, crabs, and birds live among its roots."},{"id":"Pohon bakau bisa hidup di air laut yang asin.","en":"Mangrove trees can live in salty seawater."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/6ff699218b04654d.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/c211ef295f34d967.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9e46ea2e529bcdeb.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/b4e2647dc204423d.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/d5e6a33f64a65b39.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/570c9435a9932759.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9e46ea2e529bcdeb.jpg","credit":"Ron from Nieuwegein / South Moreton Oxfordshire, Netherlands / UK","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/570c9435a9932759.jpg","credit":"Ulf Mehlig","license":"CC BY-SA 2.5"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b4e2647dc204423d.jpg","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d5e6a33f64a65b39.jpg","credit":"Wie146","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6ff699218b04654d.jpg","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c211ef295f34d967.jpg","credit":"CEphoto, Uwe Aranas","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hutan_mangrove"},"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_jalak_bali_1","title_id":"Jalak Bali","title_en":"Bali Myna","subtitle_id":"Burung putih cantik kebanggaan Pulau Bali","subtitle_en":"Bali's beautiful white pride bird","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Jalak Bali?","h_en":"What Is the Bali Myna?","body_id":"Jalak bali adalah burung pengicau cantik berukuran sedang, panjangnya sekitar 25 cm. Burung ini hanya ditemukan di hutan bagian barat Pulau Bali. Ia satu-satunya hewan asli khas Bali, jadi sangat istimewa. Pada tahun 1991, jalak bali dipilih menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali.","body_en":"The Bali myna is a beautiful medium-sized songbird, about 25 cm long. This bird is found only in the forests of western Bali. It is the only animal native to Bali, so it is very special. In 1991, the Bali myna was chosen as the official animal symbol of Bali Province."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Bulu jalak bali hampir seluruhnya berwarna putih bersih. Hanya ujung sayap dan ekornya yang berwarna hitam. Di sekeliling matanya ada pelupuk berwarna biru tua yang sangat cantik. Burung jantan punya jambul indah di kepalanya.","body_en":"The Bali myna's feathers are almost entirely pure white. Only the tips of its wings and tail are black. Around its eyes is a lovely deep-blue patch. The male has a beautiful crest on its head."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Jalak bali suka tinggal di hutan mangrove, hutan rawa, dan daerah savana. Rumah aslinya ada di Taman Nasional Bali Barat. Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon, cukup tinggi dari tanah. Burung ini suka terbang berombongan bersama teman-temannya.","body_en":"The Bali myna loves to live in mangrove forests, swamp forests, and savanna areas. Its natural home is in West Bali National Park. It builds its nest inside tree holes, fairly high off the ground. This bird loves to fly in flocks with its friends."},{"icon":"favorite","h_id":"Kebiasaan Lucu","h_en":"Fun Habits","body_id":"Jalak bali punya kicauan khas berupa siulan dan lengkingan yang nyaring. Ia bahkan pandai menirukan suara burung lain! Burung ini sangat suka kebersihan dan senang bermain air untuk mandi. Setelah mandi, ia berjemur di bawah sinar matahari agar bulunya kering dan berkilau.","body_en":"The Bali myna has a special song of whistles and bright, ringing calls. It is even good at copying the sounds of other birds! This bird loves cleanliness and enjoys splashing in water to bathe. After bathing, it suns itself so its feathers dry and shine."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jalak bali termasuk burung yang sangat langka di alam liar. Jumlahnya pernah menurun sampai tinggal sedikit sekali. Untungnya, banyak orang baik bekerja keras menjaga dan menangkarkannya. Yuk, kita sayangi jalak bali agar burung cantik ini terus berkicau di Bali!","body_en":"The Bali myna is a very rare bird in the wild. Its numbers once dropped down to very few. Luckily, many kind people work hard to protect and breed them. Let's care for the Bali myna so this beautiful bird keeps singing in Bali!"}],"facts":[{"id":"Jalak bali adalah satu-satunya hewan khas asli Bali!","en":"The Bali myna is the only animal native to Bali!"},{"id":"Bulunya hampir 90 persen berwarna putih bersih.","en":"About 90 percent of its feathers are pure white."},{"id":"Ia menjadi lambang fauna Provinsi Bali sejak 1991.","en":"It has been Bali Province's animal symbol since 1991."},{"id":"Jalak bali pandai menirukan suara burung lain.","en":"The Bali myna is good at copying other birds' sounds."},{"id":"Ia membuat sarang di dalam lubang pohon.","en":"It builds its nest inside tree holes."},{"id":"Burung ini sangat suka mandi dan menjaga kebersihan.","en":"This bird loves bathing and staying clean."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/a6fa2ef43c702575.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/000c823cf42ebd18.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/8e23caa6af095eb7.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/1e55d1be9f083cac.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/a1f732fe3d3dd789.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a6fa2ef43c702575.jpg","credit":"JJ Harrison","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/000c823cf42ebd18.jpg","credit":"No machine-readable author provided. Stavenn assumed (based on copyright claims)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/1e55d1be9f083cac.jpg","credit":"en:User:Cburnett","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8e23caa6af095eb7.jpg","credit":"Ady Kristanto","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a1f732fe3d3dd789.jpg","credit":"en:User:Cburnett","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jalak_bali"},"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar":{"id":"ensiklopedia_kantong_semar","title_id":"Kantong Semar","title_en":"Pitcher Plant","subtitle_id":"Tumbuhan ajaib pemakan serangga!","subtitle_en":"A magical insect-eating plant!","sections":[{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Apa Itu Kantong Semar?","h_en":"What Is the Pitcher Plant?","body_id":"Kantong semar adalah tumbuhan yang memakan serangga! Para ilmuwan menyebut kelompoknya Nepenthes. Tumbuhan ini punya kantong berisi cairan khusus yang bisa melarutkan serangga kecil. Dari serangga itulah ia mendapat makanan tambahan.","body_en":"The pitcher plant is a plant that eats insects! Scientists call its group Nepenthes. It has a pouch filled with a special liquid that can dissolve tiny insects. That is how it gets extra food."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Kantong semar suka tempat lembap seperti rawa-rawa. Ia tumbuh di Indonesia, terutama di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Di Kalimantan Barat, orang menyebutnya entuyut. Ada yang hidup di pantai, ada pula yang tinggi di pegunungan.","body_en":"Pitcher plants love damp places like swamps. They grow in Indonesia, especially on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. In West Kalimantan, people call it entuyut. Some live near the beach, and others live high in the mountains."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Kantong semar memanjat tanaman lain dan bisa tumbuh sangat tinggi. Di ujung daunnya ada sulur yang berubah menjadi kantong perangkap. Ada kantong atas yang tinggi untuk menangkap nyamuk dan lalat. Ada juga kantong bawah dekat tanah untuk menjebak semut.","body_en":"Pitcher plants climb other plants and can grow very tall. At the tip of each leaf is a tendril that turns into a trap-pouch. The upper pouch hangs high to catch mosquitoes and flies. The lower pouch sits near the ground to trap ants."},{"icon":"water_drop","h_id":"Cara Lembut Menangkap Serangga","h_en":"How It Gently Traps Insects","body_id":"Bibir kantong licin dan harum, jadi serangga datang untuk mencicipi. Saat menginjak tepi yang licin, serangga tergelincir masuk ke dalam kantong. Di dalam ada cairan berenzim yang perlahan mengubah serangga menjadi makanan. Begitulah tumbuhan ini mendapat nutrisi tanpa harus berburu.","body_en":"The rim of the pouch is slippery and sweet-smelling, so insects come for a taste. When they step on the slick edge, they slide down into the pouch. Inside is a special liquid that slowly turns the insect into food. That is how the plant gets nutrients without hunting."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Kantong semar tumbuh di tanah miskin makanan, jadi ia pintar mencari nutrisi sendiri. Bahkan kelelawar kecil suka tidur di dalam kantongnya yang aman! Karena unik, kita harus menjaga rawa dan hutan tempatnya hidup. Dengan melindungi rumahnya, tumbuhan ajaib ini bisa terus tumbuh.","body_en":"Pitcher plants grow in soil that is poor in food, so they cleverly find their own nutrients. Tiny bats even like to sleep safely inside their pouches! Because they are so unique, we must protect the swamps and forests where they live. By saving their home, this magical plant can keep growing."}],"facts":[{"id":"Kantong semar memakan serangga, bukan dimakan serangga!","en":"The pitcher plant eats insects instead of being eaten by them!"},{"id":"Ada lebih dari 100 jenis kantong semar di dunia.","en":"There are more than 100 kinds of pitcher plants in the world."},{"id":"Kelelawar berbulu wol suka tidur aman di dalam kantongnya.","en":"Woolly bats like to sleep safely inside the pouch."},{"id":"Cairan di dalam kantong bisa melarutkan serangga kecil.","en":"The liquid inside the pouch can dissolve tiny insects."},{"id":"Di Kalimantan, kantongnya dipakai sebagai wadah membuat kue!","en":"In Borneo, the pouch is used as a container for making cakes!"},{"id":"Ada kantong semar yang tumbuh tinggi di gunung, lebih dari 3.000 meter!","en":"Some pitcher plants grow high on mountains, over 3,000 meters up!"}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/3c337722596ebff7.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/e2749697e68a1792.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/4ebbe0488c825f13.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/0beaf77174ac2dc2.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/d13d9119b96f364a.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9bdd040f0158e1fb.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3c337722596ebff7.jpg","credit":"Kleo Marlo Sialongo","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e2749697e68a1792.jpg","credit":"en:User:Rbrtjong","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d13d9119b96f364a.jpg","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9bdd040f0158e1fb.jpg","credit":"Ariefrahman","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/4ebbe0488c825f13.jpg","credit":"Pavel Kirillov from St.Petersburg, Russia","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/0beaf77174ac2dc2.jpg","credit":"NoverKelana","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kantong_semar"},"ensiklopedia_komodo_2":{"id":"ensiklopedia_komodo_2","title_id":"Komodo","title_en":"Komodo Dragon","subtitle_id":"Kadal terbesar di dunia dari Indonesia!","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest lizard, from Indonesia!","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Komodo?","h_en":"What Is the Komodo Dragon?","body_id":"Komodo adalah biawak raksasa dan kadal terbesar di dunia! Panjangnya bisa 2 sampai 3 meter, sepanjang sebuah mobil kecil. Orang asli pulau Komodo menyebutnya ora. Hewan ini hanya hidup di Indonesia, jadi kita patut bangga!","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a giant monitor lizard and the biggest lizard in the world! It can be 2 to 3 meters long, about as long as a small car. The local people of Komodo Island call it ora. This animal lives only in Indonesia, so we can be proud!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Komodo hanya hidup di beberapa pulau di Nusa Tenggara Timur, Indonesia. Pulau-pulaunya bernama Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, dan Gili Dasami. Mereka suka padang rumput terbuka dan hutan belukar. Tempat tinggalnya kini dilindungi sebagai Taman Nasional Komodo.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon lives only on a few islands in East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia. The islands are called Komodo, Rinca, Flores, Gili Motang, and Gili Dasami. They like open grasslands and bushy forests. Their home is now protected as Komodo National Park."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Komodo punya kulit tebal berwarna abu-abu sampai cokelat dan ekor sepanjang tubuhnya. Lidahnya panjang dan bercabang, dipakai untuk mencium bau dari jauh. Komodo bahkan bisa mencium bangkai dari jarak beberapa kilometer! Cakarnya kuat untuk menggali lubang tempat berlindung.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon has thick gray-to-brown skin and a tail as long as its body. Its long, forked tongue is used to smell from far away. A Komodo can even smell food from several kilometers away! Its strong claws help dig burrows for shelter."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Komodo adalah pemakan daging, dan sering memakan bangkai yang sudah mati. Ia suka menyendiri dan hanya berkumpul saat makan atau berkembang biak. Walau besar, komodo bisa berlari cepat, berenang, bahkan menyelam. Saat masih muda, ia juga pandai memanjat pohon dengan cakarnya.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a meat-eater and often feeds on animals that have already died. It likes to be alone and only gathers to eat or to breed. Even though it is big, it can run fast, swim, and even dive. When young, it is also good at climbing trees with its claws."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Komodo adalah hewan langka yang hanya ada di Indonesia, jadi sangat istimewa. Sayangnya rumahnya makin sempit karena ulah manusia. Pemerintah melindunginya dan membuat Taman Nasional Komodo. Dengan menjaga hutan dan pulaunya, komodo bisa hidup bahagia untuk waktu yang lama.","body_en":"The Komodo dragon is a rare animal found only in Indonesia, so it is very special. Sadly, its home is getting smaller because of people. The government protects it and created Komodo National Park. By caring for its forests and islands, the Komodo dragon can live happily for a long time."}],"facts":[{"id":"Komodo adalah kadal terbesar di dunia!","en":"The Komodo dragon is the biggest lizard in the world!"},{"id":"Lidahnya yang bercabang bisa mencium bau dari berkilo-kilometer jauhnya.","en":"Its forked tongue can smell from kilometers away."},{"id":"Komodo bisa berlari hingga 20 km per jam dalam jarak pendek.","en":"A Komodo can run up to 20 km per hour over short distances."},{"id":"Ia pandai berenang dan bisa menyelam sedalam 4,5 meter.","en":"It is a good swimmer and can dive 4.5 meters deep."},{"id":"Komodo punya sekitar 60 gigi tajam di mulutnya.","en":"A Komodo has about 60 sharp teeth in its mouth."},{"id":"Komodo hanya hidup liar di Indonesia, tidak di tempat lain di dunia!","en":"Komodo dragons live in the wild only in Indonesia, nowhere else!"}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/7d2a3b45ec0eb402.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/14ec90a093111f14.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/d5599131a75bee94.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/d9c808ccbd1c5e2b.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/3fa168ccf872fe14.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/7d2a3b45ec0eb402.jpg","credit":"Charles J. Sharp","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3fa168ccf872fe14.jpg","credit":"Phyzome","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/14ec90a093111f14.jpg","credit":"Markofjohnson at English Wikipedia","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d5599131a75bee94.jpg","credit":"Wikimedia Commons","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/d9c808ccbd1c5e2b.jpg","credit":"Markofjohnson","license":"CC0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Komodo"},"ensiklopedia_orangutan":{"id":"ensiklopedia_orangutan","title_id":"Orang Utan","title_en":"Orangutan","subtitle_id":"Kera cerdas penghuni pohon hutan hujan!","subtitle_en":"The clever ape of the rainforest trees!","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Orang Utan?","h_en":"What Is the Orangutan?","body_id":"Orang utan adalah kera besar berbulu cokelat kemerahan. Namanya berasal dari bahasa Melayu yang berarti orang hutan. Ada tiga jenis orang utan: Kalimantan, Sumatra, dan Tapanuli. Mereka adalah saudara jauh kita yang sangat pintar.","body_en":"The orangutan is a great ape with reddish-brown hair. Its name comes from the Malay words meaning person of the forest. There are three kinds of orangutan: Bornean, Sumatran, and Tapanuli. They are our clever distant cousins."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Orang utan hidup di hutan hujan Indonesia dan Malaysia. Sekarang mereka hanya ditemukan di pulau Kalimantan dan Sumatra. Mereka adalah kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon. Hampir sepanjang hari dihabiskan di antara dahan-dahan yang tinggi.","body_en":"Orangutans live in the rainforests of Indonesia and Malaysia. Today they are found only on the islands of Borneo and Sumatra. They are the great apes that love living in trees the most. Almost all day is spent high among the branches."},{"icon":"height","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Orang utan punya lengan yang sangat panjang dan kaki yang pendek, sempurna untuk berayun di pohon. Tubuhnya tertutup rambut cokelat kemerahan. Orang utan jantan dewasa lebih besar dan punya bantalan lebar di kedua pipinya. Jantan juga sering berteriak panjang yang terdengar dari jauh.","body_en":"Orangutans have very long arms and short legs, perfect for swinging through trees. Their bodies are covered in reddish-brown hair. Adult males are bigger and have wide pads on their cheeks. Males also make long calls that can be heard from far away."},{"icon":"restaurant","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Makanan kesukaan orang utan adalah buah-buahan. Mereka juga makan daun, kulit kayu, madu, serangga, dan telur burung. Orang utan sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk membantu mencari makan. Setiap malam mereka membuat sarang baru dari ranting dan daun untuk tidur.","body_en":"The orangutan's favorite food is fruit. They also eat leaves, tree bark, honey, insects, and bird eggs. Orangutans are very smart and can use tools to help find food. Every night they build a new nest from twigs and leaves to sleep in."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Kenapa Istimewa & Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Why It's Special & Let's Protect It","body_id":"Orang utan adalah salah satu primata paling cerdas di dunia. Sayangnya ketiga jenisnya kini sangat terancam punah. Hutan tempat tinggalnya banyak ditebang, dan itu membuat mereka kehilangan rumah. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu orang utan tetap hidup bebas dan bahagia.","body_en":"Orangutans are among the smartest primates in the world. Sadly, all three kinds are now in great danger of disappearing. Many of their forests have been cut down, leaving them without a home. By protecting the forests, we help orangutans stay free and happy."}],"facts":[{"id":"Orang utan berarti orang hutan dalam bahasa Melayu.","en":"Orangutan means person of the forest in Malay."},{"id":"Mereka kera besar yang paling suka tinggal di atas pohon.","en":"They are the great apes that love living in trees the most."},{"id":"Orang utan membuat sarang baru dari ranting setiap malam.","en":"Orangutans build a new nest from twigs every night."},{"id":"Mereka sangat pintar dan bisa memakai alat untuk mencari makan.","en":"They are very clever and can use tools to find food."},{"id":"Orang utan bisa hidup lebih dari 30 tahun.","en":"Orangutans can live more than 30 years."},{"id":"Lengan orang utan lebih panjang daripada kakinya untuk berayun.","en":"An orangutan's arms are longer than its legs for swinging."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/b30a1e77d5d9e4fc.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/c430a7d4906c53b7.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/63fb91ec52199d0b.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/479e288fefe8bc8c.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/53d9f15b8104e8b9.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/6a5563ea6efb2051.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b30a1e77d5d9e4fc.jpg","credit":"Eleifert","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/53d9f15b8104e8b9.jpg","credit":"George Edwards","license":"Public domain"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/c430a7d4906c53b7.jpg","credit":"Eric Kilby, Aiwok, Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/6a5563ea6efb2051.jpg","credit":"Ghedoghedo","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/63fb91ec52199d0b.jpg","credit":"Tim Laman","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/479e288fefe8bc8c.jpg","credit":"Michel wal","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orang_utan"},"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1":{"id":"ensiklopedia_penyu_hijau_1","title_id":"Penyu Hijau","title_en":"Green Sea Turtle","subtitle_id":"Penyu laut besar yang jelajahi samudra hangat","subtitle_en":"A big sea turtle roaming warm oceans","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Penyu Hijau?","h_en":"What Is a Green Sea Turtle?","body_id":"Penyu hijau adalah penyu laut yang besar. Ia hidup di laut dan membawa rumahnya sendiri, yaitu cangkang yang kuat. Namanya 'hijau' karena ada lemak berwarna hijau di bawah cangkangnya, bukan karena cangkangnya hijau!","body_en":"The green sea turtle is a large sea turtle. It lives in the ocean and carries its own home, a strong shell. It is called 'green' because of the green fat under its shell, not because the shell is green!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Penyu hijau berenang di laut hangat di seluruh dunia, terutama di Samudra Atlantik dan Samudra Pasifik. Ia suka air tropis dan subtropis yang hangat. Di Indonesia, penyu ini dirawat dan ditangkarkan di Ujung Genteng, Sukabumi.","body_en":"Green sea turtles swim in warm oceans all around the world, especially the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans. They love warm tropical and subtropical waters. In Indonesia, they are cared for and bred at Ujung Genteng in Sukabumi."},{"icon":"shield","h_id":"Tubuh & Ciri Khas","h_en":"Body & Features","body_id":"Penyu hijau punya cangkang keras di atas tubuhnya untuk melindungi diri. Kaki-kakinya berbentuk seperti dayung supaya bisa berenang cepat di air. Ia bernapas dengan paru-paru, jadi harus naik ke permukaan untuk menghirup udara.","body_en":"The green sea turtle has a hard shell on top of its body for protection. Its legs are shaped like paddles so it can swim quickly through the water. It breathes with lungs, so it must come up to the surface for air."},{"icon":"eco","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan","h_en":"Food & Habits","body_id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan tumbuhan laut, seperti rumput laut dan lamun. Itulah sebabnya ia sering disebut penyu pemakan tumbuhan. Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir, lalu bayi-bayi kecilnya menetas dan bergegas menuju laut.","body_en":"Adult green sea turtles love eating sea plants, such as seaweed and seagrass. That is why they are known as plant-eating turtles. Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand, then the tiny babies hatch and hurry to the sea."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Jumlah penyu hijau makin sedikit karena diburu untuk cangkang, telur, dan dagingnya. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga laut dan pantai tetap bersih. Jika kita semua peduli, penyu hijau bisa terus berenang bahagia di laut.","body_en":"Green sea turtles are becoming fewer because they are hunted for their shells, eggs, and meat. We can help by keeping the sea and beaches clean. If we all care, green sea turtles can keep swimming happily in the ocean."}],"facts":[{"id":"Namanya 'hijau' karena lemak hijau di bawah cangkangnya!","en":"It is called 'green' because of the green fat under its shell!"},{"id":"Penyu hijau adalah satu-satunya spesies dalam golongan Chelonia.","en":"The green sea turtle is the only species in the Chelonia group."},{"id":"Kakinya seperti dayung untuk berenang di laut.","en":"Its legs are like paddles for swimming in the sea."},{"id":"Induk penyu kembali ke pantai untuk bertelur di pasir.","en":"Mother turtles return to the beach to lay eggs in the sand."},{"id":"Penyu hijau dewasa suka makan rumput laut dan lamun.","en":"Adult green sea turtles love to eat seaweed and seagrass."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/a0443bdd8b758053.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/8665f0e91260185d.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/55b6d280e713b6d1.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/e3dc74e7f0e3cb54.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/3f165b798896b430.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/68d165ddba524d71.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/a0443bdd8b758053.jpg","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/68d165ddba524d71.jpg","credit":"David Monniaux","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/55b6d280e713b6d1.jpg","credit":"Brocken Inaglory","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/e3dc74e7f0e3cb54.jpg","credit":"Tokugawapants at English Wikipedia + PiccoloNamek (Modifie version)","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/8665f0e91260185d.jpg","credit":"E bailey","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3f165b798896b430.jpg","credit":"P.Lindgren","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Penyu_hijau"},"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii":{"id":"ensiklopedia_rafflesia_arnoldii","title_id":"Rafflesia Arnoldii (Padma Raksasa)","title_en":"Rafflesia Arnoldii","subtitle_id":"Bunga terbesar di dunia dari hutan Indonesia","subtitle_en":"The world's biggest flower from Indonesia's forests","sections":[{"icon":"local_florist","h_id":"Apa Itu Rafflesia?","h_en":"What Is Rafflesia?","body_id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia! Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa mencapai sekitar 70 sampai 110 sentimeter, kira-kira selebar ban mobil. Bunga raksasa ini juga salah satu bunga nasional kebanggaan Indonesia.","body_en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world! When it blooms, it can grow about 70 to 110 centimeters wide, roughly as wide as a car tire. This giant flower is also one of Indonesia's proud national flowers."},{"icon":"forest","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Rafflesia tumbuh di hutan hujan yang lembap di Pulau Sumatra dan Kalimantan. Daerah Bengkulu dikenal sebagai 'Bumi Rafflesia' karena bunga ini pertama ditemukan di sana. Taman Nasional Kerinci Seblat adalah tempat penting untuk menjaganya.","body_en":"Rafflesia grows in the damp rainforests of Sumatra and Borneo. The Bengkulu area is known as the 'Land of Rafflesia' because the flower was first found there. Kerinci Seblat National Park is an important place that protects it."},{"icon":"spa","h_id":"Bunga Tanpa Daun & Akar","h_en":"A Flower With No Leaves or Roots","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat unik karena tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunganya saja! Karena tak punya daun, ia tidak bisa membuat makanan sendiri. Jadi ia hidup menempel pada tumbuhan merambat bernama Tetrastigma dan mengambil makanan dari sana, seperti tamu yang menumpang.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very unusual because it has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower! Because it has no leaves, it cannot make its own food. So it lives attached to a climbing vine called Tetrastigma and takes food from it, like a guest borrowing a meal."},{"icon":"schedule","h_id":"Mekar & Baunya","h_en":"Blooming & Its Smell","body_id":"Rafflesia punya lima kelopak besar berwarna merah dengan bintik-bintik putih. Bunga ini hanya mekar sekitar satu minggu, lalu layu. Baunya kuat seperti bau busuk, jadi orang menyebutnya 'bunga bangkai'. Bau itu memanggil lalat untuk membantu menyebarkan benih bunga.","body_en":"Rafflesia has five big red petals with white spots. The flower blooms for only about one week, then it wilts. It smells strong like something rotten, so people call it the 'corpse flower'. That smell calls flies to help the flower make seeds."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Rafflesia sangat langka dan terancam punah karena hutan tempatnya hidup banyak ditebang. Sejak tahun 1993, bunga ini dilindungi sebagai puspa langka Indonesia. Kita bisa membantu dengan menjaga hutan tetap utuh agar bunga raksasa ini terus mekar.","body_en":"Rafflesia is very rare and endangered because the forests where it lives are being cut down. Since 1993, this flower has been protected as a rare flower of Indonesia. We can help by keeping forests safe so this giant flower can keep blooming."}],"facts":[{"id":"Rafflesia arnoldii adalah bunga terbesar di dunia!","en":"Rafflesia arnoldii is the biggest flower in the world!"},{"id":"Saat mekar, lebarnya bisa sampai 70-110 cm dan beratnya sekitar 11 kilogram.","en":"When open it can be 70-110 cm wide and weigh about 11 kilograms."},{"id":"Bunganya hanya mekar sekitar satu minggu lalu layu.","en":"The flower blooms for only about one week, then wilts."},{"id":"Baunya seperti bangkai, itu sebabnya disebut 'bunga bangkai'.","en":"It smells rotten, which is why it's called the 'corpse flower'."},{"id":"Rafflesia tidak punya daun, akar, atau batang, hanya bunga!","en":"Rafflesia has no leaves, roots, or stem, just the flower!"},{"id":"Namanya dari Thomas Stamford Raffles dan Dr. Joseph Arnold.","en":"It is named after Thomas Stamford Raffles and Dr. Joseph Arnold."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/385c30fce59c6dae.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/5bdda5cecc92b796.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/968a36f5e2a1bef9.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/df932888e453e9ab.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/3f06e227b7900dd1.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/512eff53f752a947.jpg"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/385c30fce59c6dae.jpg","credit":"Maizal Chaniago","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5bdda5cecc92b796.jpg","credit":"SofianRafflesia","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/968a36f5e2a1bef9.jpg","credit":"PlusMinus","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/df932888e453e9ab.jpg","credit":"ma_suska","license":"CC BY 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/3f06e227b7900dd1.jpg","credit":"Moheen Reeyad","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/512eff53f752a947.jpg","credit":"Moheen Reeyad","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Padma_raksasa"},"ensiklopedia_tarsius":{"id":"ensiklopedia_tarsius","title_id":"Tarsius","title_en":"Tarsier","subtitle_id":"Primata mungil bermata besar dari Sulawesi","subtitle_en":"A tiny big-eyed primate from Sulawesi","sections":[{"icon":"pets","h_id":"Apa Itu Tarsius?","h_en":"What Is a Tarsier?","body_id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, kerabat jauh dari monyet dan manusia. Tubuhnya mungil dan bisa muat di telapak tangan orang dewasa. Walau kecil, tarsius punya mata yang sangat besar dan menggemaskan!","body_en":"The tarsier is a very small primate, a distant relative of monkeys and humans. Its tiny body can fit in an adult's palm. Even though it is small, the tarsier has huge, adorable eyes!"},{"icon":"public","h_id":"Di Mana Hidupnya?","h_en":"Where Does It Live?","body_id":"Tarsius berasal dari pulau-pulau di Asia Tenggara. Genus Tarsius ini ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi, Indonesia. Mereka tinggal di pohon-pohon dalam hutan yang rimbun.","body_en":"Tarsiers come from islands in Southeast Asia. The genus Tarsius is found on the island of Sulawesi, Indonesia. They live up in the trees of leafy forests."},{"icon":"visibility","h_id":"Mata Raksasa & Tubuh","h_en":"Giant Eyes & Body","body_id":"Mata tarsius sangat besar dibanding tubuhnya, membantunya melihat dalam gelap. Ia punya jari-jari panjang untuk berpegangan erat di dahan pohon. Tarsius juga bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang untuk melihat sekeliling.","body_en":"A tarsier's eyes are huge compared to its body, helping it see in the dark. It has long fingers for gripping tree branches tightly. A tarsier can also turn its head far around to look behind itself."},{"icon":"dark_mode","h_id":"Makanan & Kebiasaan Malam","h_en":"Food & Night Habits","body_id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang. Dengan mata besarnya, ia berburu serangga seperti jangkrik dan belalang. Ia melompat dengan lincah dari satu dahan ke dahan lain untuk menangkap makanan.","body_en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day. With their big eyes, they hunt insects like crickets and grasshoppers. They leap nimbly from branch to branch to catch their food."},{"icon":"volunteer_activism","h_id":"Ayo Lindungi!","h_en":"Let's Protect It!","body_id":"Tarsius adalah hewan istimewa yang hanya hidup di tempat tertentu, jadi kita harus menjaganya. Hutan tempat tinggalnya perlu dilindungi agar tarsius punya rumah yang aman. Dengan menjaga hutan, kita membantu tarsius tetap melompat bahagia.","body_en":"The tarsier is a special animal that lives only in certain places, so we must take care of it. The forests it lives in need protection so the tarsier has a safe home. By protecting forests, we help tarsiers keep leaping happily."}],"facts":[{"id":"Tarsius adalah primata yang sangat kecil, bisa muat di telapak tangan.","en":"The tarsier is a tiny primate that can fit in your palm."},{"id":"Matanya sangat besar untuk melihat dalam gelap.","en":"Its eyes are very big for seeing in the dark."},{"id":"Tarsius aktif di malam hari dan tidur saat siang.","en":"Tarsiers are active at night and sleep during the day."},{"id":"Ia bisa memutar kepalanya jauh ke belakang.","en":"It can turn its head far around to look behind."},{"id":"Semua tarsius dari genus ini ditemukan di Pulau Sulawesi.","en":"All tarsiers of this genus are found on the island of Sulawesi."}],"gallery":["app/assets/img/wiki/5cc5af4876e10978.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/bf0952f593d2b213.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/b236a82bf73fa6db.jpg","app/assets/img/wiki/9445c5b2e40f3505.png","app/assets/img/wiki/899e3a6d844737cd.png","app/assets/img/wiki/bfcbe53d56dabc6d.png"],"credits":[{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/5cc5af4876e10978.jpg","credit":"Lip Kee Yap","license":"CC BY-SA 2.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/9445c5b2e40f3505.png","credit":"Chermundy","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bf0952f593d2b213.jpg","credit":"Meldy Tamenge","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/899e3a6d844737cd.png","credit":"Chermundy","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/b236a82bf73fa6db.jpg","credit":"Illustratedjc","license":"CC BY-SA 4.0"},{"src":"app/assets/img/wiki/bfcbe53d56dabc6d.png","credit":"Chermundy","license":"CC BY-SA 3.0"}],"source":"https://id.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tarsius_%28genus%29"}};
